The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New York, Oct. 28 (PTI): An Indian was among two persons arrested in the US for trying to provide arms and ammunition to the Lebanon-based terrorist group Hezbollah.          
	Patrick Nayyar, 46, who had been illegally staying in New York, has also been charged with possessing firearms.                  
	 Allahabad (PTI): The Centre has sanctioned a project to develop helicopters that are less vulnerable to crashes. The Motilal Nehru National Institute of Technology, which has been entrusted with the project, is developing a twin-control rotor system with reduced design errors and enhanced trajectory precision.                   
	 Bangalore (PTI): The telecom department has issued a directive banning all handsets that do not carry the legitimate International Mobile Equipment Identify number provided by the Indian Cellular Association, the mobile industrys apex body. The 15-digit code identifies a mobile phone and helps prevent use of stolen handsets by enabling security agencies to track down the user.                  dore (PTI): A woman has allegedly burnt to death her husband, suspecting he had an extramarital affair. Jyoti poured kerosene on Pappu Bhagirath, 35, and set him on fire while he slept after one of their frequent quarrels.                  
	 Ooty (PTI): Forest department officials have seized 55 stuffed heads of wild animals kept without licence in a club in Ooty. The officials raided the 100-year-old Ooty Club and seized 40 stuffed deer heads and 15 fox heads.                  
	 Ahmedabad (PTI): Two workers were killed and another seriously injured when a lift carrying them collapsed at the site of an under-construction power project in Gujarats Kutch district on Wednesday. The lift collapsed because of a technical fault, police said.                                                                                                                           
